review_blob: At first taste beer was syrupy, a bit fruity with a present alcohol taste.  I thought it tasted interesting, but a bit much to drink a whole bottle.  Upon second try thoughts of cough syrup (specifically nyquil) entered my mind and affected my palate to the point where I can no longer not associate this beer with that taste...
Deep brown in color.  Very malty brown ale with a hint of caramel flavor.  Smooth finish, a solid beer for a nitrogen tap.
Really good on Nitro Tap.  This beer is soo smooth with choco, coffee, malty flavors.  Very dark brown looks like dark melted chocolate, awesome beer!!!

beer_brewer_name: Coney Island Brewing Company (Boston Beer Company)
review_blob: Very interesting beer.  Tastes like a mixture between a lager and an amber.  Darker in color than most lagers.  The full body mixed with amber taste makes for a nice experience on your palate.
Tastes almost more like a soda, with a tart taste.  Not my type of beer, but I can still see why people like it.  Smooth, refreshing, flavorful, different beer...
Awesome IPA on draft.  A little darker in color, delicious aroma and good flavor.  Smooth, but still has the hops bitter bite.
Smooth like an Amber but a strong hoppy bitter bite to it.  Awesome balance between flavors.  Try it on Nitro, on of the few hoppy beers I think the nitro smoothness improves!
Drinks more like an IPA than a pale ale.  Hops explosion in ur mouth.  Very flavorful does a great job covering up the high alcohol content and after one or two ur feeling a nice warm, chatty buzz.
beer_name: Mountain Sun XXX American Pale Ale

review_blob: Nothing to rave about, but nothing to complain about.  Taste is very bland, but also refreshing and easy to drink.  Very little aroma or flavor with a very clear golden appearance.  Near the end I noticed a very slight pilsner-esque after taste (kinda tastes like a blander Stella).
Smooth, refreshing taste, like a buttery pilsner.  Very easy to drink, but much more flavor than the average lager.
beer_name: Samuel Smiths Pure Brewed Organic Lager

review_blob: Very bold flavor smells like a fruity alcoholic syrup.  Can taste the bite of high alcohol content, but the intense smell and flavor help cover it.  Takes a few sips to adjust to such a different flavor, but at the end your feeling good and wanting more.
